\begin_layout Subsection*
Geometric Interpretation of Vectors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Saying that Victor drove 5 kilometers describes how far he drove.
 In the terminology of physics, the magnitude or length of his drive was
 5 kilometers.
 Saying that Victor drove 5 kilometers due east describes how far he drove
 and which way.
 In the terminology of physics, the magnitude of his drive was 5 kilometers
 and the direction of his drive was due east.
 This information can be captured by the vector 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
5\\
0
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset

by interpreting this vector as Victor's displacement or movement in what
 would be the horizontal and vertical directions on a map pointing due north.
