\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
The vector is the hypotenuse of a right triangle with side lengths 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{\frac{9}{2}}$
\end_inset

, which by the Pythagorean theorem gives it length 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{\left(\sqrt{\frac{9}{2}}\right)^{2}+\left(\sqrt{\frac{9}{2}}\right)^{2}}=3$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Victor's total displacement or movement for the drive, as the crow flies,
 is represented by the sum of the vectors,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\begin{array}{c}
5+\sqrt{\frac{9}{2}}\\
-\sqrt{\frac{9}{2}}
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

